{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The scoring model assigns the correct risk score when a transaction exceeds the configured amount threshold for its merchant category.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A pure unit test of scoring math can miss real failures in category-to-threshold config wiring (wrong key, stale config parse, default fallback). The failure boundary is scoring logic + configuration source together.","test_description":"Run the scoring pipeline against a real local config fixture (same format/parser used in production) containing per-category thresholds. Submit a transaction above its category threshold and assert the produced numeric risk score matches expected weighted rule output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk model identifies a fraudulent transaction pattern (e.g., rapid small purchases from different geographies) even when no single rule threshold is exceeded.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on the real fraud model’s learned behavior, not deterministic rule code. Mocking or stubbing the model can always pass while hiding true model-serving/model-output failures on this pattern.","test_description":"Call the real deployed (or production-equivalent) risk model with a crafted transaction sequence showing rapid low-value purchases across distant geographies while rule thresholds remain under limits. Assert fraud probability crosses the fraud flag threshold. Run repeatedly with acceptance band/tolerance for model variability.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The velocity check in the scoring model correctly counts the number of transactions within the configured time window per user.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Time-window counting commonly fails at storage/query/time-boundary wiring (timestamp precision, timezone, inclusive/exclusive bounds). In-process mocks can miss these data-layer boundary errors.","test_description":"Use a local transactional store with real query path. Insert timestamped transactions for one user around the window edges, execute velocity scoring, and assert the counted transactions and resulting velocity contribution are correct for configured window semantics.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A transaction flagged by the risk model but not by the scoring model is still held for review — the models operate as an OR gate, not AND.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk here is orchestration/wiring: combining two model outputs and routing to review hold. A unit test of a boolean helper can miss contract mismatches between model outputs and decision layer.","test_description":"Wire real scoring and risk decision modules (or production-equivalent adapters). Feed a case where scoring is below hold threshold and risk model returns fraud-flag true, then assert transaction status is set to hold-for-review.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The combined output includes both the numeric risk score and the risk model's fraud probability, so the reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a schema/composition contract across modules (scoring output + risk output + response serializer). Mock-only unit tests can miss dropped/renamed fields in real composition.","test_description":"Execute the combined decision endpoint/service with real serializers/mappers and assert output payload contains both `risk_score` (numeric) and `fraud_probability` (numeric), plus flag source indicators reflecting which model triggered review.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
